Ahead of the election days on February 25 and March 11, the Independent National Electoral Commission has urged potential voters to find their polling units. This article from PunchMetro shows you how to find your polling unit. Step 1: Go to either voters.inecnigeria.org or cvr.inecnigeria.org on the INEC website. Step 2: Use the online form to find your polling unit and voter status. Step 3: To find directions to your voting location, click the green link. Step 4: Use the map or directions on your phone to find your voting location. Remember that the directions given are approximations. It is advised that you go to your polling unit before election day.